org.junit.platform.engine

Interface ConfigurationParameters


  • @API(value=Experimental)
public interface ConfigurationParameters
    Configuration parameters that TestEngines may use to influence test discovery and execution.

    For example, the JUnit Jupiter engine uses a configuration parameter to enable IDEs and build tools to deactivate conditional test execution.

    Since:
    1.0
    See Also:
    TestEngine, EngineDiscoveryRequest, ExecutionRequest

    • Method Detail

      • get

        java.util.Optional<java.lang.String> get(java.lang.String key)
        Get the configuration property stored under the specified key.

        If no such key is present in this ConfigurationParameters, an attempt will be made to look up the value as a Java system property.

        Parameters:
        key - the key to look up; never null or blank
        Returns:
        an Optional containing the potential value

      • size

        int size()
        Get the number of configuration properties stored directly in this ConfigurationParameters.
